						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Kharapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅgachōḷa III. Year 30: 1207-08 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription seems to record a gift of land (detailst lost), made free of taxes such as <hi rend="italic">kāśāyam, āśuvikkaḍamai, āḷamañji tēvai</hi> etc., as <hi rend="italic">jīvitam</hi> to Aṅgada-vallavar, at Tiruppāṟkaḍal, a southern hamlet of Kāvirippākkam. The donor's name is lost.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
